The surface diagnostics from an
atmospheric model simulation that used AMIP boundary conditions.

Date: Wed, 2 Nov 1994 15:42:26 -0500
From: cmglr@isis.giss.nasa.gov (Gary L. Russell)
To: benno@ldgo.columbia.edu
Subject: AMIP data

Dear Benno,

I have an account on rosie under the account "cmrun".  There is a
subdirectory "AMIP" which contains the surface diagnostics from an
atmospheric model simulation that used AMIP boundary conditions.  In my
account on cmrun are two fortran programs and their executable modules:
MEAN4X5 and QDF.  "QDF AMIP/EVAP" will list on the console the title of
each record of the file.  "MEAN4X5 AMIP/EVAP 12" will list on the console
the mean values of the 12-th record of the file.  Call me if you have
additional questions.

Sincerely, Gary Russell

\begin{ingrid}
/AMIP insertdataset:
/iridl:hasSemantics (iriref:Russell_GL) def
/name /AMIP def
/source (Run C027AM) def
/contact (Gary L. Russell <I>cmglr@isis.giss.nasa.gov</I>)def
/description (The surface diagnostics from an atmospheric model simulation with AMIP boundary conditions.) def
grid:
/name /X def
degE
